article.headline: Ole Miss cruises to big win in first round of Hurricane Classic
article.linkText: Ole Miss cruises to big win over Black Bears
article.story:
CORAL GABLES, Florida (Ticker) -- Armintie Price scored 18 
points and grabbed 11 rebounds as No. 25 Mississippi coasted to 
a 72-52 victory over Maine in the first round of the Hurricane 
Holiday Classic.

The Lady Rebels (10-2) used a dominant defensive performance in 
the opening half to advance to Thursday's championship game 
against either Miami or North Carolina AT.

The Black Bears (2-6) shot just 16 percent (4-of-25) from the 
floor in the opening 20 minutes as Ole Miss raced to a 42-20 
halftime lead.

Price was 9-of-14 from the field and had five of the Lady 
Rebels' 17 turnovers. Ashley Johnson chipped in 10 points and 
three steals as Ole Miss forced 22 turnovers to rebound from a 
loss at Louisiana Tech on December 20.

Abby Schrader paced Maine with 12 points and 12 boards and 
Ashley Underwood added 11 points on 3-of-15 shooting. Leading 
scorer Bracey Barker was limited to six points and had four 
turnovers in 31 minutes in the Black Bears' sixth straight loss.
